Mutations in three genes, APP, presenilin-1 (PS1) and presenilin-2 (PS2), are
 associated with early-onset familial forms of Alzheimer's disease that are
 transmitted as an autosomal dominant
 (Goate et al, 1991;
 Levy-Lehad et al,
 1995; Sherrington et
 al, 1995). Homozygosity for a common variant of PS1, the
 1-allele, has been associated with increased risk of Alzheimer's disease in
 some, but not at all, studies
